headline: Our Amphenol Pick Just Hit a Rough Patch. Stick With It.
summary: After a strong run,  Amphenol  suffered a setback when it reported earnings last week.  Investors should hold on to the stock.  As companies from  Alphabet  to  Oracle  build out data centers to power AI programs, demand for connectors increases, to the direct benefit of suppliers like Amphenol.

headline: Amphenol Expands Fiber Reach With CommScope Deal And AI Data Center Push
summary: Amphenol (NYSE:APH) has agreed to acquire CommScope’s Connectivity and Cable Solutions division, representing a major move in fiber optic interconnects. The deal significantly expands Amphenol’s footprint in fiber solutions used in AI infrastructure and cloud data centers. The transaction is being framed as one of Amphenol’s largest acquisitions and a meaningful shift in its product mix.
